Speaker 2: Hey, my name is Ariel Carlotto.

Speaker 1: Uh, so yeah, I get them. I get the ABGs.

Speaker 2: Periodically, like once a month, but I wanted to cancel. They try to hit my card to get more, to give me more.

Speaker 1: Okay, and you're located at 120 Salvia Street, Browns Mill, New Jersey 0801?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I see you here. Yeah, so, um, you always have the option—

Speaker 2: To place your prescription on hold.

Speaker 1: For up to six months at a time, just because six months is when the prescription would expire.

Speaker 2: If we didn't refill it.

Speaker 1: And the way that would work is—

Speaker 2: It sounds like you'll be out of commission for a few months.

Speaker 1: But if you did want to order before then, you could. You just have to give us a call.

Speaker 2: Yeah, because actually, so the reason why I get up is because I ended up—I don't know if you know about this—

Speaker 1: I guess I'll know in six months if I'm gonna need them again. If I need them again—

Speaker 2: I would call you up, you know, order again.

Speaker 2: As often as I thought I would.

Speaker 1: Hello, hello. Yes. Okay, I hear you now. Sorry. Yes, I can hear you. No, totally fine. Okay.

Speaker 2: So, um, I'll place your prescription on hold for you then until the middle of August. If you need anything before then—

Speaker 1: Um, just give us a call. We're always here Monday through Friday, eight to five specifically.

Speaker 2: Appreciate it very much. Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Ariel. I hope you have a great day.

Speaker 2: You as well.
